Read Flow — licensing and attribution
======================================

Read Flow is a multi-crate workspace released under a split license. Which
license applies depends on the component:

GPL-3.0-or-later
----------------
  - read-flow          (cosmic/  — the desktop application)
  - read-flow-widgets  (widgets/ — shared desktop UI widgets)

  The full text is in LICENSE-GPL.

  These components, and any binary built from them (including the
  `read-flow` desktop app and its `--headless` server mode), are covered
  by the GNU General Public License, version 3 or later.

MIT
---
  - read-flow-core     (core/)
  - provider           (provider/)
  - epub               (epub/)
  - read-flow-pwa      (pwa/)

  The full text is in LICENSE-MIT.

  These components may be reused under the permissive MIT terms. Note that
  when they are linked into the GPL-3.0-or-later desktop application, the
  resulting combined binary is governed by the GPL.


